org.semanticweb.rulewerk.parser

Class LocalPrefixDeclarationRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.model.implementation.AbstractPrefixDeclarationRegistry
      • org.semanticweb.rulewerk.parser.LocalPrefixDeclarationRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Map.Entry<String,String>>, PrefixDeclarationRegistry

    public final class LocalPrefixDeclarationRegistry
extends AbstractPrefixDeclarationRegistry
    Implementation of PrefixDeclarationRegistry that is used when parsing data from a single source. In this case, attempts to re-declare prefixes or the base IRI will lead to errors.
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch

        public void setPrefixIri(String prefixName,
                         String prefixIri)
                  throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Description copied from interface: PrefixDeclarationRegistry
        Registers a prefix declaration. Behaviour is implementation-defined if prefixName has already been registered.
        Parameters:
        prefixName - the name of the prefix.
        prefixIri - the IRI of the prefix.
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - when prefixName is already registered, at the discretion of the implementation.

      • setBaseIri

        public void setBaseIri(String baseIri)
                throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Sets the base namespace to the given value. This should only be done once, and not after the base namespace was assumed to be an implicit default value.
        Parameters:
        baseIri - the new base namespace
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - if base was already defined
